This paper deals with intervehicle communication and the transmission of messages between vehicles. It involves the use of wireless communication and the analysis of transmission times and propagation speeds. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the use of probability distributions and analytical models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper involves the use of simulations, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
